OL,3,CNext government must close anti-
OL,4,Ccorruption 'loopholes', say MPs
OL,6,FBut while the MPs acknowledged
OL,7,Fprogress in recent years, including
OL,8,Fthe passage of two Economic Crime
OL,9,FActs, they said there were still "a
OL,10,Flong way to go before the UK can stem
OL,11,Fthe flow of dirty money".
OL,13,FVeteran Labour MP and anti-corruption
OL,14,Fcampaigner Dame Margaret Hodge said:
OL,15,F"With a general election this year,
OL,16,Fall parliamentarians ` both old and
OL,17,Fnew ` will have to work to ensure that
OL,18,Fthe UK is no longer the destination of
OL,19,Fchoice for criminals, kleptocrats and
OL,20,Ffraudsters.
